ack zone or easement"}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:2:props:style","children":["In practice, this means ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"virtually every functional residential deck in Loudoun County requires a permit"}],". Even deck resurfacing projects may require a permit if the existing structure doesn't meet current code (e.g., missing joist hangers, undersized footings, or no ledger flashing)."]}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"background":"#fef2f2","border":"1px solid #fecaca","borderRadius":8,"padding":"1.25rem","marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontWeight":600,"marginBottom":"0.5rem","color":"#991b1b"},"children":"What happens if you build without a permit?"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"lineHeight":1.7,"color":"#7f1d1d","margin":0},"children":"Building without a required permit in Loudoun County is a Class 1 misdemeanor. The county can issue stop-work orders, require demolition, and impose fines. Unpermitted structures also create serious complications during home sales — title companies and buyer inspectors flag them, and lenders may refuse to finance the purchase until the issue is resolved."}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"Documents Required for a Loudoun County Deck Permit"}],["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:2:props:style","children":"A complete deck permit application in Loudoun County requires the following:"}],["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.2rem","fontWeight":600,"margin":"1.5rem 0 0.5rem"},"children":"1. Site Plan (Plot Plan)"}],["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:2:props:style","children":"A scaled drawing of your property showing the proposed deck footprint, property lines, setback lines, easements, and distances from all structures. Loudoun County requires that you show the deck's position relative to side, rear, and front setbacks. In most residential zones (R-1 through R-8), the